![First, I made a `sudo mkdir -p` to a folder named "NetowrkDrives", then I take ownership of them with `chown`. Drives were mounted with `sudo mount -a` while learning the process.](Screenshot 2025-07-24 220218.png)
Then I edited that folder's CIFS in FSTAB to make it so the disk will automatically mount on boot.

<img width="1101" height="574" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/532ef7a8-a533-4f89-8f68-21493a1f1c49" />

I then reloaded the system state to authorize the modification,...

<img width="840" height="207" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a97bcd40-fddf-441f-be5a-42fd3c98ac89" />

...and then used `df -h` and `lsblk` to check the mounted drives. 

